<subSubSection pageId="60" pageNumber="61" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="60.[151,1436,1758,2037]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1758,1785]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Aedeagal median rod basally with 1 pair of slender, apically curved, acute, lobe-like processes, and subapically with 2 pairs of slender, lobe-like processes (
<figureCitation box="[778,881,1795,1821]" captionStart="FIGURE 32" captionStartId="61.[151,250,1647,1672]" captionTargetBox="[161,1425,632,1621]" captionTargetId="figure@61.[151,1436,625,1628]" captionTargetPageId="61" captionText="FIGURE 32. Phortica (Phortica) archikappa Gong &amp; Chen, sp. nov., male.A. Epandrium and cercus (lateral view); B. Surstylus (frontal view); C. Hypandrium, aedeagus, gonopod, and aedeagal apodeme (lateral view); D. Paramere (lateral view). Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3468848" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3468848/files/figure.png" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Fig. 32C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="61" lastPageNumber="62" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="60.[151,1436,1758,2037]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1830,1857]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Description.</emphasis>
Frons with small and triangular black above, brown below. Face brown. Mesoscutum, pleura, and scutellum brown, with black patches and pollinose pattern. Male terminalia (
<figureCitation box="[1004,1088,1867,1893]" captionStart="FIGURE 32" captionStartId="61.[151,250,1647,1672]" captionTargetBox="[161,1425,632,1621]" captionTargetId="figure@61.[151,1436,625,1628]" captionTargetPageId="61" captionText="FIGURE 32. Phortica (Phortica) archikappa Gong &amp; Chen, sp. nov., male.A. Epandrium and cercus (lateral view); B. Surstylus (frontal view); C. Hypandrium, aedeagus, gonopod, and aedeagal apodeme (lateral view); D. Paramere (lateral view). Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3468848" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3468848/files/figure.png" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Fig. 32</figureCitation>
): Epandrium pubescent anteroventrally, with ca. 8 setae on posterodorsal portion per side (
<figureCitation box="[830,935,1903,1929]" captionStart="FIGURE 32" captionStartId="61.[151,250,1647,1672]" captionTargetBox="[161,1425,632,1621]" captionTargetId="figure@61.[151,1436,625,1628]" captionTargetPageId="61" captionText="FIGURE 32. Phortica (Phortica) archikappa Gong &amp; Chen, sp. nov., male.A. Epandrium and cercus (lateral view); B. Surstylus (frontal view); C. Hypandrium, aedeagus, gonopod, and aedeagal apodeme (lateral view); D. Paramere (lateral view). Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3468848" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3468848/files/figure.png" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Fig. 32A</figureCitation>
). Surstylus lacking pubescence on outer surface, with ca. 5 wedge-like prensisetae on apical margin (
<figureCitation box="[787,889,1939,1965]" captionStart="FIGURE 32" captionStartId="61.[151,250,1647,1672]" captionTargetBox="[161,1425,632,1621]" captionTargetId="figure@61.[151,1436,625,1628]" captionTargetPageId="61" captionText="FIGURE 32. Phortica (Phortica) archikappa Gong &amp; Chen, sp. nov., male.A. Epandrium and cercus (lateral view); B. Surstylus (frontal view); C. Hypandrium, aedeagus, gonopod, and aedeagal apodeme (lateral view); D. Paramere (lateral view). Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3468848" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3468848/files/figure.png" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Fig. 32B</figureCitation>
). Posterolateral lobe of hypandrium undeveloped and lacking pubescence (
<figureCitation box="[434,538,1975,2001]" captionStart="FIGURE 32" captionStartId="61.[151,250,1647,1672]" captionTargetBox="[161,1425,632,1621]" captionTargetId="figure@61.[151,1436,625,1628]" captionTargetPageId="61" captionText="FIGURE 32. Phortica (Phortica) archikappa Gong &amp; Chen, sp. nov., male.A. Epandrium and cercus (lateral view); B. Surstylus (frontal view); C. Hypandrium, aedeagus, gonopod, and aedeagal apodeme (lateral view); D. Paramere (lateral view). Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3468848" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3468848/files/figure.png" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Fig. 32C</figureCitation>
). Paramere with sparse pubescence subapically; apical process with 1 sensillum and 3 teeth; medial process slender; basal process with 1 sensillum (
<figureCitation box="[915,1020,2011,2037]" captionStart="FIGURE 32" captionStartId="61.[151,250,1647,1672]" captionTargetBox="[161,1425,632,1621]" captionTargetId="figure@61.[151,1436,625,1628]" captionTargetPageId="61" captionText="FIGURE 32. Phortica (Phortica) archikappa Gong &amp; Chen, sp. nov., male.A. Epandrium and cercus (lateral view); B. Surstylus (frontal view); C. Hypandrium, aedeagus, gonopod, and aedeagal apodeme (lateral view); D. Paramere (lateral view). Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3468848" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3468848/files/figure.png" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Fig. 32D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
